g opportunities for more information about making a gift to fsi please contact neil penick associate director for development 100 encina hall stanford university stanford ca 94305 6055 phone 650 723 8681 fax 650 723 7543 email npenick at stanford edu annual gifts of $25 and up can be made online to support fsi stanford these gifts provide unrestricted support for crucial programs and secure the institute's ability to respond quickly and appropriately to research proposals addressing emerging environmental economic and security threats around the world if you d like to make your gift online using credit card please go to giving to fsi stanford to designate fsi or one of the centers or programs here please select other on the first pull down menu then on the second page further designation you may type fsi or one of the centers or programs in the special instructions further designation box gifts to fsi are tax deductible under applicable rules the institute is part of stanford university's tax exempt status as a section 501 c 3 public charity giving opportunities center priorities giving opportunities fsi centers and programs search cisac search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages more information neil penick associate director for development and external relations support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9625 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
